) There is a powerful tool called "valgrind" used for
   detecting memory management bugs in C code. Learn 
   elementary valgrind usage and write a blog post about
   it. 

   Links:

   http://valgrind.org/docs/manual/quick-start.html#quick-start.prepare

   http://tldp.org/HOWTO/Valgrind-HOWTO/

b) Read "split.c". Complete the "split" function. Try to
   use dynamic allocation. The builtin function "strstr"
   may be used.


